<div class="travelTips">
  <h1>TRAVEL TIPS</h1>
  
  <h2>1. Planning</h2>
  <p>The Philippines is a beautiful country with numerous attractions and offers you the best in the place. However, it is important to already plan and know the places you want to visit and on what days according to your trip. This is an important part of the planning process so that you donâ€™t waste time during your trip thinking about where to go or when to go. Planning also includes you to know about the local currency, the local language, and how you are going to travel through the country.</p>
  
  <h2>2. Best Time To Visit</h2>
  <p>The Philippines attracts a lot of tourists during the dry months, that is, between November to April. It is highly recommended to travel during these months as it would allow you to view the more beautiful spots of the country and allow access to some remote islands or areas of the country. It is not advisable to visit the country during the summer months as the temperatures during this time are at its peak and could make you feel uncomfortable throughout the trip.</p>
  
  <h2>3. Know The Language</h2>
  <p>The Philippines has around 120 to 180 languages and dialects that include Filipino, English, and Spanish. Even though English is spoken in the region, there are a large number of locals who would prefer to interact in their national language, that is, Filipino. So it is important to know a little basic language before you travel to the country as it could come in handy or when needed.</p>
  
  <h2>4. Choose The Best Hotels</h2>
  <p>While the country provides you with numerous hotels with world-class facilities, it is an integral part of your trip to choose your hotel. Everyone has this question in mind of where to stay in the Philippines. Choose your hotels based on your budget and also its location. It is important to keep in mind factors like cost, facilities, and distance from the places you want to visit as well as how you will travel in the country. Some recommended hotels for an amazing stay in the Philippines are Kandaya Resort, Club Paradise Palawan, and Blue Palawan Beach Club.</p>
  
  <h2>5. Always Keep Enough Cash</h2>
  <p>Being one of the major tourist attractions, millions of people storm the country every year. It is really important to know about the currency and keep enough amount of cash with you. Though you can pay off using your cards or through other online payment methods but many locals prefer taking cash in return for the goods. So, know about the currency and carry a good amount of cash that could come in handy anytime throughout your trip.</p>
